        "i",
        "Task build, Job B: seller accepted_mints config + gate relaxation. FIRST read docs/example.md in the repo — implement exactly §'Job B' (its scope paragraph + acceptance block are the contract). Summary:\n\n1. Replace top-level MobeeConfig.mint_url with accepted_mints: Vec<String> (default [DEFAULT_MINT_URL]); a legacy mint_url in an existing config.toml migrates to accepted_mints=[that value] on load (shim near the existing migrate_dead_mint_url).\n2. Boot gate: 'must equal DEFAULT_MINT_URL' becomes 'every accepted_mints entry is allow-listed' (testnut/dev fence stays).\n3. Delete the offer mint gate (seller_daemon.rs ~:522) and retire OfferSkip::NonTestnutMint.\n4. Re-source episode.mint (journal) and TEMPORARILY build the redeem PaymentPolicy (~:812/:826) from accepted_mints. ParsedOffer.mint_url STAYS present and readable — later jobs re-point those reads.\n5. seller.rs fixture rides along (fixture-line edits only there).\n\nCLARIFICATION not yet in the doc: config ALSO has extra_mints (buyer-wallet-level allowed mints, used by wallet mints add). accepted_mints is a NEW SEPARATE field (seller payment policy) — do NOT merge or repurpose extra_mints; if the distinction needs a doc comment, write it at the field definition.\n\nNOTE: the base includes a fresh error-reason plumb in seller_daemon.rs (your own commit b76c7b2, just merged) — build on top of it, don't fight it.\n\nENVIRONMENT: if cargo missing: source /workspace/build-env.sh\n\nAcceptance = the doc's §Job B fenced block, PLUS: cargo test -p mobee-core --all-features green EXCEPT exactly the 2 known live-mint failures in mobee-core (mint down): live_testnut_fund_observes_balance_gt_zero, authorize_pay_refuses_ext_locator_via_pay_path_verifier. If the scope genuinely cannot stay inside these files, STOP and deliver a written explanation instead of code.\n\nCommit message: 'feat(seller): accepted_mints allow-list replaces single pinned mint (Task B)'. Single commit on a fork branch as usual."
